## Method D — Correspondence Analysis (CA)

**Axis:** Dimensionality Reduction  
**Parameters:** 3 EP row scores (one per EP)

```
FUNCTION fit(data, alpha=1):
    N_mat[i,j] = count of lines where EP_i=1 AND Skill_j=1   + alpha
    P_mat      = N_mat / sum(N_mat)              -- joint probability table
    r_mass     = row sums of P_mat               -- EP marginals
    c_mass     = column sums of P_mat            -- Skill marginals
    S          = Dr^{-1/2} * (P - r*c') * Dc^{-1/2}   -- standardised residuals
    U, sigma, V = SVD(S)
    row_coords = Dr^{-1/2} * U[:,0] * sigma[0]  -- Dimension 1 row coordinates

    -- Sign anchor (domain knowledge, applied every fold):
    IF Constructivism coordinate < mean(other coordinates):
        row_coords = -row_coords

    normalise row_coords to [0, 1]
    RETURN normalised EP scores (3 values)

FUNCTION predict(line, ep_scores):
    active_EPs = [i : X_ni = 1]
    IF no active EPs:
        RETURN mean(ep_scores)
    RETURN mean(ep_scores[i] for i in active_EPs)
```

**Key property:** Chi-squared metric on EP×Skill contingency table.
Sign anchored so Constructivism always maps to high EPSPI.

