## Shared Evaluation — Cross-Validation Loop

```
PROCEDURE cross_validate(method_function, data, episodes, n_folds=5):
    split episodes into 5 folds (KFold, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    fold_r, fold_mse = [], []

    FOR each fold (train_episodes, test_episodes):
        df_train = lines belonging to train_episodes
        df_test  = lines belonging to test_episodes

        pred_lines = method_function(df_train, df_test)

        -- Aggregate to episode level
        FOR each test episode e:
            EPSPI_e = mean(pred_lines for lines in episode e)
            Y_obs_e = mean(obs_skill_mean for lines in episode e)

        r   = Pearson r(EPSPI_e, Y_obs_e) across test episodes
        mse = mean((Y_obs_e - EPSPI_e)^2) across test episodes
        fold_r.append(r);  fold_mse.append(mse)

    CV_r   = mean(fold_r)
    CV_MSE = mean(fold_mse)
    RETURN CV_r, CV_MSE

NOTE: All lines from the same episode are always in the same fold.
      Beta (or theta) is re-estimated from scratch in every fold.
```

