## Shared Evaluation — Leverage Analysis

```
PROCEDURE leverage_diagnostics(EPSPI_e, Y_obs_e, episodes):
    -- OLS design matrix: X = [1 | EPSPI_e]  (E × 2)
    H_diag    = diagonal of X(X'X)^{-1}X'           -- leverage h_e
    y_hat     = OLS fitted values
    residuals = Y_obs_e - y_hat
    s²        = sum(residuals²) / (E - 2)            -- OLS MSE

    stud_resid = residuals / (sqrt(s²) * sqrt(1 - h_e))   -- studentised
    cooks_d    = (stud_resid² / 2) * (h_e / (1 - h_e))    -- Cook's D
    dffits     = stud_resid * sqrt(h_e / (1 - h_e))

    THRESHOLDS:
        high leverage : h_e    > 2*2/E  ≈ 0.082
        influential   : D_e    > 4/E    ≈ 0.082
        dffits        : |FF_e| > 2*sqrt(2/E) ≈ 0.404

    RETURN per-episode diagnostics table
```

